  "detailedBuildGuide": "
Step-by-step Detailed Build Guide for the TWICE 'Me + You' / 'Feel Special' Mod\n\nPrerequisites:\n1) Opera GX installed (latest stable).\n2) A plain-text editor (VS Code recommended).\n3) Basic image editor (Photoshop, GIMP, or free online tools).\n4) Audio editor (Audacity or similar) if you need to trim/convert songs.\n5) A folder where you will assemble your mod files.\n\nPART A — Prepare your assets (images & audio)\n1. Background Image: create or choose an image sized at least 1920x1080 (JPG or PNG). Name it `me_you_background.jpg`.\n   - Tip: export a 2:1 version for ultrawide users (3840x1080).\n2. Member Icons: create 9 square icons sized 512x512 (128x128 minimum). Save as PNG with transparent backgrounds, named exactly as in the template: `nayeon_feel_special.png`, `jeongyeon_feel_special.png`, etc.\n   - Use consistent composition and lighting per the styleGuide in the template.\n   - Add a 6–10px inner padding so the sparkle frame has breathing room.\n3. Frames & UI art: export `sparkle_gold_frame.png` at the same size as the icons (512x512), with transparent centre.\n4. Sounds: Obtain the instrumental of "Feel Special" (ensure you have rights to use it) and trim to a 10–30s loop for startup. Save as `feel_special_instrumental.mp3` (128–256 kbps).\n   - Create short, percussive click & hover sounds inspired by "Hare Hare" (10–300 ms). Export as `hare_hare_click.mp3` and `hare_hare_hover.mp3`.\n5. Optional: keyboard sound pack (loopable 50–200 ms audio files) named `keyboard.mp3`.\n\nPART B — Folder structure (exact filenames matter)\nCreate a folder `TWICE_Mod/` with the structure below (case-sensitive):\n\nTWICE_Mod/\n  mod.json  <-- copy the template (ensure file is UTF-8)\n  assets/\n    me_you_background.jpg\n    feel_special_instrumental.mp3\n    hare_hare_click.mp3\n    hare_hare_hover.mp3\n    icons/\n      nayeon_feel_special.png\n      ... (all members)\n    frames/\n      sparkle_gold_frame.png\n\nPART C — Edit `mod.json` carefully\n1. Open `mod.json` in your editor.\n2. Update any file paths that differ from your assets folder. Paths in the template are relative to the mod root (e.g., `assets/icons/nayeon_feel_special.png`).\n3. If you change color hexes, validate them are 6 hex characters (e.g., `#D4A8FF`).\n4. Set sensible volumes for audio (0.0 to 1.0).\n5. Example small validation checklist: no trailing commas in JSON, all strings quoted, and all asset files referenced actually exist.\n\nPART D — Small CSS/JS snippets (for visual polish)\nIf your mod system supports small style overrides, use these examples:\n
/* Glow effect for icons */\n.icon {\n  width: 128px;\n  height: 128px;\n  border-radius: 12px;\n  box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(212,168,255,0.55);\n  transition: box-shadow 180ms ease, transform 180ms ease;\n}\n.icon:hover {\n  transform: translateY(-4px);\n  box-shadow: 0 0 22px rgba(212,168,255,0.85);\n}\n\n/* Gold sparkle frame overlay */\n.icon-frame {\n  background-image: url('assets/frames/sparkle_gold_frame.png');\n  background-size: cover;\n}\n\nPART E — Audio handling tips\n1. Looping music: trim a clean loop and fade end→start (0.1–0.5s crossfade) to avoid clicks.\n2. Normalize audio to -1 dB for loudness consistency.\n3. Keep click/hover SFX short and lower volume than background (try 0.15 to 0.35).\n\nPART F — Loading & testing in Opera GX\n1. Open Opera GX → Settings → Advanced → Developer → Enable `Allow Mods` and `Developer Mode`.\n2. Open the Mods menu (Ctrl+Shift+E).\n3. Click `Load unpacked` → select the `TWICE_Mod` folder.\n4. Start testing:\n   - Open a new tab → does the background appear?\n   - Restart Opera GX (if necessary) → does the startup music play?\n   - Mouse over member icons → do hover sounds and glow appear?\n   - Click icon → does click sound & member select UI open?\n\nDebugging tips: check console (Developer Tools) for file-not-found errors; verify file names & JSON paths; check audio formats if playback fails.\n\nPART G — Packaging for distribution\n1. Verify licensing: confirm you have permission to distribute any copyrighted music or images.\n2. Create a zip of the mod folder (Windows PowerShell):\n   Compress-Archive -Path .\TWICE_Mod\* -DestinationPath .\TWICE_Mod.zip\n3. Rename `TWICE_Mod.zip` to `TWICE_Mod.gxmod` if required or use Opera GX export feature (recommended).\n\nPART H — Accessibility & performance checks\n1. Provide an option to mute background music.\n2. Keep background image size under 3–5 MB for faster loading; consider a progressive JPG.\n3. Optimize PNGs (use pngquant or TinyPNG) and convert large assets to WebP if supported.\n\nLegal note: Using original TWICE recordings or official artwork likely requires permission from the rights holders. For public distribution, prefer fan-art you made or licensed covers/instrumentals.\n\nIf you want, I can next: \n- build a ready-to-download ZIP with placeholder assets I generate for you, or \n- create sample icon mockups for each member (512x512 PNGs) and add them to the template so the folder is ready to load.\n
